## The Issue with Direction Calculation

The current code calculates the direction from the UFO to the shuttle like this:

```javascript
const direction = shuttle.position.clone().sub(ufo.position).normalize();
```

This gives the correct vector from the UFO to the shuttle at the moment of firing. However, there are a few potential issues:

1. The projectile might be aiming at where the shuttle is now, not where it will be (leading the target)
2. The direction might need to be adjusted to account for the shuttle's movement
3. The projectile's orientation (rotation) isn't being set to match its travel direction

## Solution

Here's an improved version of the `createUfoProjectile` function:

```javascript:c:\CODING\Games\Zero-G Fury\main.js
function createUfoProjectile(ufo) {
  if (!shuttle) return;

  // Create projectile geometry
  const geometry = new THREE.ConeGeometry(0.2, 1, 16);
  geometry.rotateX(Math.PI / 2);
  const material = new THREE.MeshPhongMaterial({
    color: 0xff3333,
    emissive: 0xff0000,
    emissiveIntensity: 0.5
  });
  const projectile = new THREE.Mesh(geometry, material);

  // Add flame effect
  const flameGeometry = new THREE.ConeGeometry(0.15, 0.5, 8);
  flameGeometry.rotateX(Math.PI / 2);
  const flameMaterial = new THREE.MeshBasicMaterial({
    color: 0xffaa00,
    transparent: true,
    opacity: 1
  });
  const flame = new THREE.Mesh(flameGeometry, flameMaterial);
  flame.position.set(0, 0, -0.6);
  projectile.add(flame);

  // Position projectile slightly in front of the UFO (not inside it)
  const ufoToShuttle = shuttle.position.clone().sub(ufo.position).normalize();
  const spawnOffset = ufoToShuttle.clone().multiplyScalar(3); // Start 3 units in front of UFO
  projectile.position.copy(ufo.position).add(spawnOffset);

  // Calculate direction toward shuttle with some lead targeting
  // Estimate where the shuttle will be in a short time
  const shuttleVelocity = new THREE.Vector3(0, 0, -shuttleSpeed);
  const timeToTarget = projectile.position.distanceTo(shuttle.position) / 12; // Rough estimate
  const predictedShuttlePosition = shuttle.position.clone().add(
    shuttleVelocity.clone().multiplyScalar(timeToTarget * 0.5) // 50% lead targeting
  );

  // Direction to the predicted position
  const direction = new THREE.Vector3()
    .subVectors(predictedShuttlePosition, projectile.position)
    .normalize();

  // Add slight inaccuracy to make it possible for player to dodge
  direction.x += (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.1;
  direction.y += (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.1;
  direction.normalize();

  // Set projectile orientation to match travel direction
  projectile.lookAt(projectile.position.clone().add(direction));

  // Calculate projectile velocity
  const projectileSpeed = 12; // Faster than shuttle
  const velocity = direction.clone().multiplyScalar(projectileSpeed);

  // Add shuttle's velocity component to make projectile movement relative to world, not shuttle
  velocity.add(shuttleVelocity);

  // Store velocity and metadata
  projectile.userData = {
    velocity: velocity,
    fromUfo: true,
    creationTime: performance.now()
  };

  // Add to scene and tracking array
  scene.add(projectile);
  ufoProjectiles.push(projectile);

  // Add light trail effect
  const trail = new THREE.PointLight(0xff0000, 1, 10);
  projectile.add(trail);

  // Debug visualization (temporary)
  console.log("UFO projectile fired:", 
    "From:", ufo.position.toArray().map(v => v.toFixed(1)),
    "To:", predictedShuttlePosition.toArray().map(v => v.toFixed(1)),
    "Dir:", direction.toArray().map(v => v.toFixed(2))
  );
}
```

