    }

    requestAnimationFrame(pulseAnimation);
  }

  // Start the animation
  requestAnimationFrame(pulseAnimation);
}
```

The key changes are:

1. Defined all the variables (`expanding`, `minScale`, `maxScale`, `pulseDuration`, and `startTime`) before they're used in the `pulseAnimation()` function.

2. Made sure these variables are in the same scope as the `pulseAnimation()` function so they can be accessed.

3. Initialized `startTime` with `performance.now()` before the first call to `pulseAnimation()`.

This ensures that all variables are properly defined and initialized before they're used, which will resolve the "startTime is not defined" error.

