This approach:

1. Uses HTML elements that are already present in your HTML file
2. Applies CSS styling to those elements
3. Adds JavaScript event listeners to the existing elements
4. Maintains all the functionality (flashing, shaking, etc.)
5. Updates the display when inventory changes

This is more maintainable as it separates the HTML structure from the JavaScript logic, making it easier to modify the appearance without changing the code.

