 *       - Set start command: `npm start`
 *       - Add environment variable: MONGODB_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
 * 
 *    b) Heroku:
 *       - Create a new app
 *       - Connect your GitHub repository
 *       - Add MongoDB Atlas as an add-on or use external MongoDB
 *       - Set environment variable: MONGODB_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
 * 
 *    c) Vercel:
 *       - Install Vercel CLI: `npm i -g vercel`
 *       - Run `vercel` in the project directory
 *       - Set environment variable: MONGODB_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
 * 
 * 3. MongoDB Setup:
 *    - For local: Install MongoDB and start the service
 *    - For production: Create a MongoDB Atlas account (free tier available)
 *      - Create a new cluster
 *      - Create a database user
 *      - Whitelist IP addresses (0.0.0.0/0 for all IPs)
 *      - Get connection string and replace <password> with your password
