The backend is designed to be easily deployed to various hosting platforms, and the frontend gracefully handles connectivity issues.

I understand you want to interact directly with MongoDB from your JavaScript frontend without creating a separate backend. This approach has some limitations and security concerns, but there are a few options:

## Option 1: MongoDB Atlas Data API

MongoDB Atlas (the cloud version of MongoDB) offers a Data API that allows you to interact with your database directly from frontend JavaScript using REST API calls.

Here's how to implement this:

```javascript:c:\CODING\Games\Zero-G Fury\main.js
